Name: n-Undecane
Description: Undecane is a straight-chain alkane with 11 carbon atoms.

animal_concentrations.Value: The concentration of n-undecane in tissue samples collected from 12 wolves /Canis lupus signatus/ of Northern Spain was determined to be 6.29 mg/kg lipid weight in suprarenal capsule and 6.31 mg/kg lipid weight in muscle(1).

fish_seafood_concentrations.Value: Thirteen species of fish collected from the Arabian Gulf during 1985 were found to contain n-undecane concentrations in muscle ranging from 0.1 (Tylosurus strongylurus; Johnieops sina) to 0.3 ug/g dry weight (Eleutheronema tetradactum; Thryssa hamiltonii; Arius thalassinus; Acanthopagrus latus; Nematalosa nasus)(1). n-Undecane was found in samples of adult lake trout (Salvelinus namaycush) and walleye (Stizostedion v. vitreum) collected in 1977 from Lake Michigan, Lake Superior, and Lake St. Clair, quantity unknown(2). The average concentrations of n-undecane in a limpet (Patella ulyssiponensis) taken from three sampling sites between 1991-1993 on the island of Tenerife in the Canary Islands were 501.5, 1,305, and 1,469 ng/g dry weight (3). The concentrations of n-undecane in fish obtained from markets in the cities of Matrah, Aseeb, and Sur in Oman, located on the Arabian Peninsula, in February and July of 1995 ranged between 0.19 and 0.74 mg/kg wet weight(4).

sediment_soil_concentrations.Value: SEDIMENT: In the heavily industrialized area of Kitakyushu, Japan, n-undecane was detected but not quantified in sediment(1). n-Undecane was detected in bank filtrate near Karlsruhe, Germany, at average concentrations of 50 ng/L (1-4 meter depth) and 60 ng/L (16-18 meter depth), as compared to a concentration of 80 ng/L in the Rhine River at the same location(2). Surface sediments collected from the Shinano River in Niigata, Japan between November 2005 and April 2006 contained n-undecane concentrations of <0.2 to 16 ng/g dry weight(3). n-Undecane was detected in cover soil at a landfill near Florence, Italy at levels of <2 to 182 ppbv(4).
